Paper: hep-th/9301122

Date: 1993-01-29

Title: Hiding Anomalies

Authors: F. De Jonghe, R. Siebelink and W. Troost

Comments: 10p

Journal-ref: Phys. Lett. B306 (1993) 295

Anomalies can be anticipated at the classical level without changing theclassical cohomology, by introducing extra degrees of freedom. In the process,the anomaly does not quite disappear. We show that, in fact, it is shifted tonew symmetries that come with the extra fields.